sei Pisemsky’s One Thousand Souls (1858), and Vasily Sleptsov’s Hard Times (1865). Challenging much current scholarly consensus about the social dynamics of nineteenth-century realist fiction, Sovereign Fictions offers an important intervention in socially inflected theories of the novel and in current thinking on representations of power and historical poetics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079731240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226831886423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226831886/original  a978-3-11-079731-2  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles